Nigerian striker Ekundayo Ebenezer Mawoyeka Nigerian striker Ekundayo Ebenezer Mawoyeka has reportedly died of heart attack during a match between his club, Sarayköyspor and Yeşilköyspor on Sunday in Turkey. The 23-years old suffered heart attack in the 35th minute of play and died in hospital Sunday night. Denizli Amateur Sports Clubs Federation President, Feyyaz Ceşen, in a statement, described Mawoyeka’s death as sad. First responders said that the Nigerian striker died of heart attack. His death led to the postponement of the match. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .